article.headline: Radford defeats Longwood 86-75
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- R.J. Price scored 28 points to lead Radford over Longwood 86-75 on Wednesday. Javonte Green added 22 points and 13 rebounds for the Highlanders (18-10, 8-5 Big South), while Ya Ya Anderson had 14. Radford shot 48 percent from the floor, including 9 of 22 from beyond the arc. Radford led by eight early but Longwood used a 10-0 run, including Tristan Carey's 3-pointer, to lead by one at intermission, 39-38. Longwood's Jeylani Dublin tied the game at 68 with a jumper, but Price made a pair of free throws and Green hit a jumper to put Radford back up by four. Carey's dunk and subsequent free throw cut it to one. Anderson responded with a trey, and Price's layup and free throw made it a five-point game with 1:39 left. Radford sealed the win at the free throw line. Lucas Woodhouse led Longwood (8-20, 3-10) with 19 points.
